Sure! Here's a Java function that uses the Transliterator class from the ICU4J library to transliterate Cyrillic text to Latin:

```
import com.ibm.icu.text.Transliterator;

public class CyrillicToLatin {
    public static String transliterate(String cyrillicText) {
        Transliterator toLatinTrans = Transliterator.getInstance("Cyrillic-Latin");
        return toLatinTrans.transliterate(cyrillicText);
    }
}
```

You can use this function like this:

```
String cyrillicText = "Здравей свят!";
String latinText = CyrillicToLatin.transliterate(cyrillicText);
System.out.println(latinText);
```

This will output "Zdravey svyat!", which is the Latin transliteration of the Cyrillic text.

